  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law and national laws on money laundering intersect through various mechanisms and frameworks:\n\n1. Key International Organizations and Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- International Monetary Fund (IMF) guidelines\n\n2. Mutual Legal Assistance Mechanisms:\n- Cross-border cooperation agreements\n- Extradition treaties\n- Information sharing protocols between financial intelligence units\n\n3. Standardization of Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Regulations:\n- Common reporting standards\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting mechanisms\n\n4. Legal Compliance Requirements:\n- Banks and financial institutions must adhere to international AML standards\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk transactions\n\n5. Enforcement and Sanctions:\n- International sanctions against countries with weak AML frameworks\n- Coordinated investigations across jurisdictions\n- Asset freezing and seizure mechanisms\n\n6. Technology and Information Sharing:\n- Digital platforms for cross-border financial intelligence\n- Blockchain and cryptocurrency tracking\n- Enhanced data analytics for detecting illicit financial flows\n\nThis intersection creates a complex, multi-layered approach to combating money laundering globally.",
